<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>SRM | Sénégal — Three Scenarios · 25 May 2026</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,600;0,700;1,600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@300;400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
:root{
  --ink:#010d18;--gold:#c9a84c;--gold2:#e8c56a;
  --white:#f2ede4;--muted:#6b87a8;
  --red:#c8303a;--amber:#c97b06;--green:#0d7a4a;--terra:#b84a28;
}
html,body{width:100%;height:100%;overflow:hidden;background:var(--ink);font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;}
canvas.bgc{position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;z-index:0;}

.deck{position:relative;width:100%;height:100%;}
.slide{position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;
  opacity:0;pointer-events:none;overflow:hidden;
  transition:opacity .65s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1),transform .65s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1);
  transform:translateX(70px) scale(0.98);}
.slide.active{opacity:1;pointer-events:all;transform:translateX(0) scale(1);}
.slide.exit{opacity:0;transform:translateX(-70px) scale(0.98);}
.slide::after{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;z-index:2;pointer-events:none;
  background:repeating-linear-gradient(0deg,transparent,transparent 3px,rgba(0,0,0,.05) 3px,rgba(0,0,0,.05) 4px);}

/* BRACKETS */
.bk{position:absolute;z-index:4;width:22px;height:22px;pointer-events:none;}
.bk-tl{top:13px;left:13px;border-top:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;}
.bk-tr{top:13px;right:13px;border-top:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;}
.bk-bl{bottom:52px;left:13px;border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;}
.bk-br{bottom:52px;right:13px;border-bottom:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;}

/* GHOST */
.ghost{position:absolute;z-index:1;font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-weight:700;
  line-height:.85;color:transparent;pointer-events:none;user-select:none;
  text-transform:uppercase;white-space:nowrap;}

/* NAV */
.progress-bar{position:absolute;bottom:0;left:0;height:2px;
  background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--terra),var(--gold));transition:width .6s ease;z-index:10;}
.nav{position:absolute;bottom:16px;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;z-index:20;}
.nav-btn{width:33px;height:33px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(201,168,76,.08);
  border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.25);color:var(--gold);cursor:pointer;font-size:13px;
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;transition:background .2s,transform .15s;user-select:none;}
.nav-btn:hover{background:rgba(201,168,76,.2);transform:scale(1.1);}
.dot{width:5px;height:5px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(201,168,76,.22);cursor:pointer;transition:all .3s;}
.dot.active{background:var(--gold);transform:scale(1.5);}
.snum{position:absolute;bottom:20px;right:38px;z-index:20;
  font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;color:rgba(201,168,76,.3);letter-spacing:.15em;}

/* ── COVER ── */
.cv-inner{position:relative;z-index:3;flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:flex-end;padding:0 52px 68px;}
.cv-tag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.28em;color:var(--gold);
  text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;opacity:0;animation:fup .7s .2s forwards;}
.cv-title{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(44px,6.5vw,90px);font-weight:600;
  color:var(--white);line-height:.9;margin-bottom:20px;opacity:0;animation:fup .7s .35s forwards;}
.cv-title em{color:var(--gold);font-style:italic;}
.cv-title span{color:var(--terra);}
.cv-rule{width:68px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--terra),var(--gold));
  margin-bottom:18px;opacity:0;animation:expw .7s .5s forwards;}
.cv-sub{font-size:14px;font-weight:300;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7;max-width:560px;
  margin-bottom:26px;opacity:0;animation:fup .7s .6s forwards;}
.cv-pills{display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;opacity:0;animation:fup .7s .8s forwards;}
.pill{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.13em;
  border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.3);color:var(--gold);padding:6px 14px;text-transform:uppercase;}
.pill-r{border-color:rgba(200,48,58,.4);color:var(--red);}
.cv-dg{position:absolute;top:0;right:0;width:38%;height:100%;z-index:1;
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,transparent,rgba(184,74,40,.05));
  clip-path:polygon(24% 0,100% 0,100% 100%,0% 100%);}
.cv-dl{position:absolute;top:0;right:0;width:38%;height:100%;z-index:1;
  border-left:1px solid rgba(184,74,40,.1);clip-path:polygon(24% 0,100% 0,100% 100%,0% 100%);}

/* ── SCENARIO SLIDE ── */
.sc-wrap{position:relative;z-index:3;flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;padding:32px 52px 28px;}
.sc-topbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;
  padding-bottom:13px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.15);margin-bottom:22px;}
.sc-brand{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.2em;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;}
.sc-date{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.1em;}

/* scenario number badge */
.sc-badge{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;margin-bottom:18px;}
.sc-num{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(60px,8vw,100px);font-weight:700;
  line-height:1;color:transparent;-webkit-text-stroke:1px;}
.sc-label-wrap{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:5px;}
.sc-label{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.22em;
  text-transform:uppercase;}
.sc-name{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,34px);font-weight:600;color:var(--white);line-height:1.05;}

/* probability bar */
.prob-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:20px;}
.prob-label{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.15em;color:var(--muted);text-transform:uppercase;white-space:nowrap;}
.prob-bar{flex:1;height:4px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.06);border-radius:2px;}
.prob-fill{height:100%;border-radius:2px;transition:width 1s ease;}
.prob-pct{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:500;}

/* content grid */
.sc-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:14px;flex:1;}
.sc-box{padding:16px 18px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;
  background:rgba(255,255,255,.02);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.07);position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.sc-box::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;}
.sb-title{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:8.5px;letter-spacing:.18em;
  text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;}
.sb-narrative{font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#8dadc8;line-height:1.7;}
.sb-narrative strong{color:var(--white);}

/* indicators list */
.ind-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;}
.ind-item{display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start;}
.ind-dot{width:5px;height:5px;border-radius:50%;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:6px;}
.ind-text{font-size:12.5px;font-weight:300;color:#7a9ab2;line-height:1.55;}
.ind-text strong{color:var(--white);}

/* sahel impact box */
.sahel-box{grid-column:1/-1;padding:14px 18px;display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start;
  border:1px solid;position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.sahel-box::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;}
.sahel-icon{font-size:18px;flex-shrink:0;padding-top:2px;}
.sahel-label{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:8.5px;letter-spacing:.18em;
  text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:5px;}
.sahel-text{font-size:13px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.65;}
.sahel-text strong{color:var(--white);}

/* COLORS PER SCENARIO */
/* S1 — green/theatre */
.s1-num{-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgba(13,122,74,.5);}
.s1-label{color:var(--green);}
.s1 .sc-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--green),transparent);}
.s1 .sb-title{color:var(--green);}
.s1 .ind-dot{background:var(--green);}
.s1 .sahel-box{background:rgba(13,122,74,.05);border-color:rgba(13,122,74,.3);}
.s1 .sahel-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--green),transparent);}
.s1 .sahel-label{color:var(--green);}
.s1 .sahel-text{color:#5ecba1;}
.s1 .prob-fill{background:var(--green);}
.s1 .prob-pct{color:var(--green);}
.s1 .bk-tl,.s1 .bk-tr,.s1 .bk-bl,.s1 .bk-br{border-color:rgba(13,122,74,.4);}

/* S2 — amber/power struggle */
.s2-num{-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgba(201,124,6,.5);}
.s2-label{color:var(--amber);}
.s2 .sc-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--amber),transparent);}
.s2 .sb-title{color:var(--amber);}
.s2 .ind-dot{background:var(--amber);}
.s2 .sahel-box{background:rgba(201,124,6,.05);border-color:rgba(201,124,6,.3);}
.s2 .sahel-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--amber),transparent);}
.s2 .sahel-label{color:var(--amber);}
.s2 .sahel-text{color:#d4aa40;}
.s2 .prob-fill{background:var(--amber);}
.s2 .prob-pct{color:var(--amber);}
.s2 .bk-tl,.s2 .bk-tr,.s2 .bk-bl,.s2 .bk-br{border-color:rgba(201,124,6,.4);}

/* S3 — red/coup */
.s3-num{-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgba(200,48,58,.5);}
.s3-label{color:var(--red);}
.s3 .sc-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--red),transparent);}
.s3 .sb-title{color:var(--red);}
.s3 .ind-dot{background:var(--red);}
.s3 .sahel-box{background:rgba(200,48,58,.06);border-color:rgba(200,48,58,.3);}
.s3 .sahel-box::before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--red),transparent);}
.s3 .sahel-label{color:var(--red);}
.s3 .sahel-text{color:#c09090;}
.s3 .prob-fill{background:var(--red);}
.s3 .prob-pct{color:var(--red);}
.s3 .bk-tl,.s3 .bk-tr,.s3 .bk-bl,.s3 .bk-br{border-color:rgba(200,48,58,.4);}

/* ── CLOSING ── */
.cl-inner{flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;align-items:center;
  text-align:center;padding:0 52px;position:relative;z-index:3;}
.cl-tag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.28em;color:var(--gold);
  text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;}
.cl-title{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(36px,5.5vw,72px);font-weight:600;
  color:var(--white);line-height:.92;margin-bottom:14px;}
.cl-title em{color:var(--gold);font-style:italic;}
.cl-rule{width:52px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--terra),var(--gold));margin:0 auto 16px;}
.cl-body{font-size:13.5px;font-weight:300;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7;max-width:420px;margin-bottom:24px;}
.cl-cards{display:flex;gap:9px;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:22px;}
.cl-card{padding:10px 16px;border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.22);min-width:125px;}
.cl-cl{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:8px;letter-spacing:.15em;color:var(--muted);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:3px;}
.cl-cv{font-size:13px;color:var(--gold2);}
.cl-ft{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:8.5px;color:rgba(107,135,168,.3);letter-spacing:.1em;line-height:1.8;}

/* ANIMATIONS */
@keyframes fup{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(18px);}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0);}}
@keyframes expw{from{opacity:0;width:0;}to{opacity:1;width:68px;}}
@keyframes sin{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(11px);}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0);}}
.slide.active .sc-badge{animation:sin .5s .05s both;}
.slide.active .prob-row{animation:sin .5s .15s both;}
.slide.active .sc-box:nth-child(1){animation:sin .45s .2s both;}
.slide.active .sc-box:nth-child(2){animation:sin .45s .3s both;}
.slide.active .sahel-box{animation:sin .45s .4s both;}

@media(max-width:700px){
  .cv-inner,.sc-wrap,.cl-inner{padding:20px 18px 24px;}
  .sc-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}
  .sahel-box{grid-column:1;}
  .cl-cards{flex-direction:column;align-items:center;}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="deck" id="deck">
<div class="progress-bar" id="pb"></div>
<div class="snum" id="sn">01 / 05</div>
<div class="nav"><div class="nav-btn" id="prev">&#8592;</div><div class="nav-dots" id="nd"></div><div class="nav-btn" id="next">&#8594;</div></div>

<!-- ═══ SLIDE 1: COVER ═══ -->
<div class="slide active" id="s0">
  <canvas class="bgc" id="c0"></canvas>
  <div class="ghost" style="font-size:28vw;bottom:-5%;left:-2%;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(201,168,76,.055);">SN</div>
  <div class="cv-dg"></div><div class="cv-dl"></div>
  <div class="bk bk-tl" style="border-color:rgba(201,168,76,.4);"></div>
  <div class="bk bk-tr" style="border-color:rgba(201,168,76,.4);"></div>
  <div class="bk bk-bl" style="border-color:rgba(201,168,76,.4);"></div>
  <div class="bk bk-br" style="border-color:rgba(201,168,76,.4);"></div>
  <div class="cv-inner">
    <div class="cv-tag">SRM Grand Lakes &amp; Africa &middot; Scenario Intelligence Flash</div>
    <div class="cv-title">Sénégal :<br><span>Three</span><br><em>Scenarios</em></div>
    <div class="cv-rule"></div>
    <div class="cv-sub">48 hours. Two institutions decapitated. One country at a crossroads — and a Sahel watching every move. What happens next in Dakar shapes the security architecture of West Africa.</div>
    <div class="cv-pills">
      <div class="pill">25 May 2026</div>
      <div class="pill">SRM Flash Analysis</div>
      <div class="pill pill-r">High Priority</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ SLIDE 2: SCENARIO 1 ═══ -->
<div class="slide s1" id="s1">
  <canvas class="bgc" id="c1"></canvas>
  <div class="ghost" style="font-size:20vw;top:8%;right:-2%;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(13,122,74,.06);">THÉÂTRE</div>
  <div class="bk bk-tl"></div><div class="bk bk-tr"></div><div class="bk bk-bl"></div><div class="bk bk-br"></div>
  <div class="sc-wrap">
    <div class="sc-topbar">
      <div class="sc-brand">SRM &middot; Scenario Analysis &middot; Sénégal 2026</div>
      <div class="sc-date">25 May 2026</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-badge">
      <div class="sc-num s1-num">01</div>
      <div class="sc-label-wrap">
        <div class="sc-label s1-label">Orchestrated Rupture</div>
        <div class="sc-name">"The Theatre of Conflict"</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prob-row">
      <div class="prob-label">Probability</div>
      <div class="prob-bar"><div class="prob-fill" style="width:35%;background:var(--green);"></div></div>
      <div class="prob-pct s1">35%</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-grid">
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Narrative</div>
        <div class="sb-narrative">The Faye–Sonko split is <strong>performative theatre.</strong> Both actors coordinated behind closed doors — a planned institutional separation designed to allow Faye to pivot toward France and the IMF while Sonko manages the street base. The conflict is the cover story.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Key Indicators — Watch For</div>
        <div class="ind-list">
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>No major street violence</strong> — protests stay symbolic, no sustained mobilization</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>PASTEF party discipline holds</strong> — no public fracture, no rival factions</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>IMF talks accelerate</strong> within 3–4 weeks — debt deal moves quietly forward</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>Sonko accepts "new role"</strong> publicly, no hostile moves against Faye</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sahel-box">
        <div class="sahel-icon">🟢</div>
        <div>
          <div class="sahel-label">Sahel Impact</div>
          <div class="sahel-text">Low immediate risk. Senegal stabilizes internally, maintains ECOWAS alignment. <strong>Regional terrorism unaffected.</strong> AES countries remain cautious but no catalyst for escalation.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ SLIDE 3: SCENARIO 2 ═══ -->
<div class="slide s2" id="s2">
  <canvas class="bgc" id="c2"></canvas>
  <div class="ghost" style="font-size:16vw;top:8%;right:-2%;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(201,124,6,.06);">POUVOIR</div>
  <div class="bk bk-tl"></div><div class="bk bk-tr"></div><div class="bk bk-bl"></div><div class="bk bk-br"></div>
  <div class="sc-wrap">
    <div class="sc-topbar">
      <div class="sc-brand">SRM &middot; Scenario Analysis &middot; Sénégal 2026</div>
      <div class="sc-date">25 May 2026</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-badge">
      <div class="sc-num s2-num">02</div>
      <div class="sc-label-wrap">
        <div class="sc-label s2-label">Genuine Power Struggle</div>
        <div class="sc-name">"Sonko Pivots to the Assembly"</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prob-row">
      <div class="prob-label">Probability</div>
      <div class="prob-bar"><div class="prob-fill" style="width:50%;background:var(--amber);"></div></div>
      <div class="prob-pct" style="color:var(--amber);">50%</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-grid">
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Narrative</div>
        <div class="sb-narrative">The rupture is <strong>real.</strong> Ndiaye's resignation opens the Assembly speaker seat. Sonko — fired but free, still party leader with a massive youth base — pivots to become National Assembly president. <strong>Two power centers form.</strong> Faye controls the presidency; Sonko controls the legislature.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Key Indicators — Watch For</div>
        <div class="ind-list">
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>Speaker election called</strong> — National Assembly announces timeline (Week 1)</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>Sonko declares candidacy</strong> — PASTEF mobilizes behind him (Week 2)</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>Faye blocks or delays</strong> the election — constitutional crisis threshold (Week 3)</div></div>
          <div class="ind-item"><div class="ind-dot"></div><div class="ind-text"><strong>Street mobilization</strong> — youth protests, Sonko rallies, legislative paralysis</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sahel-box">
        <div class="sahel-icon">🟡</div>
        <div>
          <div class="sahel-label">Sahel Impact</div>
          <div class="sahel-text">High regional destabilization. Senegal's internal conflict signals weakness. AES countries harden against ECOWAS. <strong>JNIM increases pressure on Senegal's eastern borders.</strong> Coastal arc (Dakar–Abidjan–Cotonou) perceived as fractured.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ SLIDE 4: SCENARIO 3 ═══ -->
<div class="slide s3" id="s3">
  <canvas class="bgc" id="c3"></canvas>
  <div class="ghost" style="font-size:16vw;top:8%;right:-2%;-webkit-text-stroke:1px rgba(200,48,58,.07);">COUP</div>
  <div class="bk bk-tl"></div><div class="bk bk-tr"></div><div class="bk bk-bl"></div><div class="bk bk-br"></div>
  <div class="sc-wrap">
    <div class="sc-topbar">
      <div class="sc-brand" style="color:var(--red);">SRM &middot; Scenario Analysis &middot; Sénégal 2026</div>
      <div class="sc-date">25 May 2026</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-badge">
      <div class="sc-num s3-num">03</div>
      <div class="sc-label-wrap">
        <div class="sc-label s3-label">Military Intervention</div>
        <div class="sc-name">"Constitutional Coup"</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prob-row">
      <div class="prob-label">Probability</div>
      <div class="prob-bar"><div class="prob-fill" style="width:25%;background:var(--red);"></div></div>
      <div class="prob-pct" style="color:var(--red);">25%</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-grid">
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Narrative</div>
        <div class="sb-narrative">If Faye and Sonko lock into open war (Scenario 2 escalates), the military — <strong>French-trained, Western-aligned</strong> — uses constitutional crisis as pretext to seize power. Senegal joins Mali, Burkina, Niger in the <strong>military junta belt.</strong> ECOWAS loses its last civilian democracy anchor in the Sahel.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-box">
        <div class="sb-title">Key Indicators — Watch For</div>
